      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean r there actually studies that show it's a major cause? it feels like a lot of people just say that to justify cutting programs, even though things like automation or just older people retiring might be bigger factors. can u find some evidence that supports the idea that these benefits are actually what's driving people out of the workforce?",
