    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but r those studies even looking at the whole picture tho? i feel like most of that research focuses way too much on the \"incentive\" part and ignores how these programs actually help people get stable enough to eventually find better work. like, isn't it also true that a lot of the decline in participation is just because of aging demographics or because people are needing to care for family? shouldn't an economic researcher give equal weight to those structural reasons instead of just blaming welfare?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
